It's a faceroll on Normal, Hard is fun, and Insane really requires you to concentrate on your upgrade order and purchase timing. First run through on insane I did without any bought characters and it took me a decent amount of time to get a top bracket score. Second time playing I tested all the bought characters and decided that there are two or three gems out of the 5 available depending on your strategy. The Dragoon will make your life much easier because he's a Tank style character with health regeneration so if you decide to buy anything buy him first. The second is a toss up between the Obsidian Knight and Night Shade. Obsidian Knight has a health steal ability which comes in handy, and Night Shade hits twice when he attacks giving you better burst damage. Personally I like the Obsidian Knight over the Night Shade but it depends on your strategy. The other two bought characters are alright but not really any better than the other unique characters you can get as you go through the game.
